WEBVTT

00:01.376 --> 00:02.878
FRANK:
Previously on Hardy Boys...

00:02.878 --> 00:04.922
CALLIE:
We need to get the power out of Frank

00:04.922 --> 00:06.298
before it destroys him.

00:06.298 --> 00:09.301
YOUNG GEORGE: They want your power.
They're going to try to take it from you.

00:09.301 --> 00:11.178
And you are so close.

00:11.178 --> 00:14.431
FENTON [on phone]: I'm being framed.
- Dixon City Police! Open up!

00:14.431 --> 00:15.807
- It's only a couple stories up.

00:15.807 --> 00:17.684
- Don't do anything crazy.

00:17.684 --> 00:20.312
- You need me to steal back the relic

00:20.312 --> 00:21.772
from Stratemeyer Global.

00:21.772 --> 00:23.357
JOE:
You bring Frank to the chamber,

00:23.357 --> 00:25.484
I'll bring the relic, we'll get the power
out of him once and for all.

00:25.484 --> 00:28.570
- The Eye told me that I need the power
to get what I want most!

00:28.570 --> 00:31.406
- And what is that?!
- I want my mom back, Joe!

00:31.406 --> 00:32.783
ANGELA:
Give up the power, Frank,

00:32.783 --> 00:34.451
and everyone walks away from this alive.

00:34.451 --> 00:36.411
[tires screech, gunfire]

00:37.120 --> 00:38.664
- Sorry, Joey. [grunts]

00:38.664 --> 00:40.457
JOE: I just wish
I could see the look on his face

00:40.457 --> 00:42.501
when he realizes
that he ran off with a fake.

00:42.501 --> 00:43.919
[groans]
[high-pitched tone]

00:43.919 --> 00:46.046
FRANK: Shadow Man's at the school.
- You have to get out of here.

00:46.046 --> 00:48.590
- I'm not going home
until I get at least one dance.

00:48.590 --> 00:50.175
♪

00:50.175 --> 00:52.094
CALLIE:
Tell us about Project Midnight.

00:52.094 --> 00:54.054
MARIAN CODY: We were attempting
to transfer one person's consciousness

00:54.054 --> 00:55.889
into another person's body.

00:55.889 --> 00:57.975
Adrian Munder was never
a part of Project Midnight.

00:57.975 --> 01:01.103
Patient B was his brother, Aaron.
They're twins.

01:01.103 --> 01:02.563
- It was Aaron who did all of this,

01:02.563 --> 01:04.398
all so that he could get
his hands on that crystal.

01:04.398 --> 01:06.859
- But why would he attack his own brother?
- He didn't!

01:06.859 --> 01:08.986
He had a bandage on his wrist
from getting stitches.

01:08.986 --> 01:10.988
BELINDA:
There's no way he could heal that fast.

01:10.988 --> 01:12.197
PHIL:
We were right the whole time.

01:12.197 --> 01:13.156
FRANK [whispers]:
George?

01:13.699 --> 01:15.158
[muffled struggling]

01:19.037 --> 01:22.040
♪

01:24.877 --> 01:26.545
[inaudible]

01:28.463 --> 01:31.466
[inaudible]

01:40.350 --> 01:42.686
♪ dance music fades in ♪

01:45.189 --> 01:47.691
- So, what was that bad thing
that was supposed to happen?

01:47.691 --> 01:48.609
- Nothing.

01:49.568 --> 01:50.485
Everything's great.

01:51.278 --> 01:52.654
CHET:
Joe! Joe!

01:53.322 --> 01:54.781
I can't find Frank.
- What?!

01:54.781 --> 01:55.782
- Come on.

01:55.782 --> 01:58.911
♪

01:58.911 --> 02:00.495
[muffled dance chatter]

02:00.495 --> 02:02.122
Angela's here. She has the tracker.

02:02.122 --> 02:03.749
- You think she has Frank?
PHIL: I figured it out!

02:03.749 --> 02:05.000
I figured it out!

02:05.792 --> 02:07.169
I figured it out.
- We figured it out.

02:07.169 --> 02:08.921
- No cuts, no stitches.
- What are you talking about?

02:08.921 --> 02:11.507
- It's not Munder in the hospital.
- Well it is, just not the Munder we know.

02:11.507 --> 02:13.467
- Mr. Munder has
an identical twin named Aaron.

02:13.467 --> 02:15.135
He was the one who went
catatonic after Project Midnight.

02:15.135 --> 02:16.720
- But how do you know?
- Did you find the nurse?

02:16.720 --> 02:19.389
- We found his nurse. Nurse Cody?
She was the one taking care of Aaron

02:19.389 --> 02:21.058
all this time,
before his brother came to get him.

02:21.058 --> 02:23.185
- Mr. Munder switched places
with his twin brother.

02:23.185 --> 02:24.770
- Mr. Munder's the Shadow Man.

02:24.770 --> 02:26.021
CALLIE and JOE:
Frank was right!

02:26.021 --> 02:27.523
- Where is Frank?
- Angela might have him.

02:27.523 --> 02:29.358
- What?!
- Frank had a vision that drew us here.

02:29.358 --> 02:31.485
- He saw someone getting attacked
by the Shadow Man at the dance.

02:31.485 --> 02:33.237
- We thought it was Lucy, but she's fine.
We were dancing.

02:33.237 --> 02:35.280
- Nice, man! What song?
- Not now, Phil!

02:35.280 --> 02:37.241
- Now, Angela's here, and--
- And you think she's got Frank?

02:37.241 --> 02:38.909
- Wait. If Angela was just tracking Frank,

02:38.909 --> 02:40.911
she would have gone to
the chamber where he had his vision.

02:40.911 --> 02:43.455
- But she came here instead.
- So she's gotta be tracking the crystal.

02:43.455 --> 02:45.374
- Yeah, because they both give off
the same energy signature.

02:45.374 --> 02:47.751
- That explains the headache
that Frank got in the chamber.

02:47.751 --> 02:49.670
Last time I saw that happen,
she had us tied up down there

02:49.670 --> 02:51.755
the day of the parade.
The day of the robbery.

02:51.755 --> 02:53.549
Her tracker lit up when
the crystal was being stolen.

02:53.549 --> 02:54.883
- Are you saying--
- I'm saying

02:54.883 --> 02:57.594
that there's a connection between
The Eye and the crystal.

02:57.594 --> 03:00.305
And if the Shadow Man has the crystal,
he must have figured out the connection

03:00.305 --> 03:02.432
and used it to lure Frank to the school.

03:02.432 --> 03:04.351
The Shadow Man has Frank.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.770
- What are we standing around for?
- He could be anywhere by now.

03:06.770 --> 03:08.897
- Where would Mr. Munder take him?
Where do we even start?

03:08.897 --> 03:11.149
- We need to go to Mr. Munder's house.
We could've missed something.

03:11.149 --> 03:12.359
- Let's go.
- Okay.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.736
- Wait, wait, wait.
We don't have to chase down Frank.

03:14.736 --> 03:16.488
We go after Angela.
- We get our hands on the tracker.

03:16.488 --> 03:18.323
- If he has another vision,
it'll lead us right to him. Let's go.

03:18.323 --> 03:20.534
♪

03:21.076 --> 03:23.120
CALLIE: You really think Mr. Munder
would bring him back here?

03:23.120 --> 03:24.371
JOE:
I just think we missed something.

03:24.371 --> 03:26.915
♪

03:26.915 --> 03:28.542
PHIL: What are we gonna
find that the cops didn't?

03:28.542 --> 03:30.961
- Well, everybody thought that Mr. Munder
was a victim of the Shadow Man,

03:30.961 --> 03:33.547
but nobody searched this place
thinking that the Shadow Man lived here.

03:33.547 --> 03:35.632
- If Mr. Munder swapped places
with his brother,

03:35.632 --> 03:37.634
he did it in a hurry
because we were closing in on him.

03:38.927 --> 03:40.637
He had no time to clean everything.

03:40.637 --> 03:42.681
- But why'd they take Frank?
- 'Cause Frank has The Eye.

03:42.681 --> 03:44.516
- Yeah, but Mr. Munder didn't know that.

03:44.516 --> 03:47.019
- Well, maybe he did.
PHIL: How?

03:49.062 --> 03:51.523
- Phil?
- What? Don't look at me like that.

03:51.523 --> 03:53.817
- Did you let it slip when you
and Mr. Munder

03:53.817 --> 03:55.652
were solving the code
on the scroll like best friends?

03:55.652 --> 03:57.321
- We are not best friends.
- Are you sure?

03:57.321 --> 03:58.405
- Yeah, Biff's my best friend.

03:58.405 --> 03:59.907
CALLIE:
Are you sure you didn't tell him?

03:59.907 --> 04:02.242
- No, no chance! No! What?

04:02.242 --> 04:03.243
JOE:
It was me.

04:03.243 --> 04:05.078
♪

04:05.078 --> 04:06.580
When we found Aaron,

04:07.456 --> 04:09.082
I was talking to Phil.

04:09.082 --> 04:10.792
I said that Frank
had the power of The Eye in him.

04:11.418 --> 04:13.754
- Wait, that means that Mr. Munder
must've been in the house.

04:13.754 --> 04:15.339
- Creepy.

04:15.339 --> 04:17.758
- So, what? He was hiding?

04:17.758 --> 04:20.677
He had to be in earshot.
- Over here.

04:23.847 --> 04:27.100
- Okay, guys,
this is where we were standing.

04:27.935 --> 04:29.770
[echoing]: I just don't get it.
I mean, Frank was so sure,

04:29.770 --> 04:31.647
even with the power of The Eye in him.

04:31.647 --> 04:33.565
[sighs] We have no idea who we're chasing.

04:37.653 --> 04:39.780
[click, creaking]

04:41.198 --> 04:42.199
[coat hangers rattling]

04:45.661 --> 04:47.162
[clicking]

04:49.206 --> 04:50.999
[door creaking]

04:52.960 --> 04:54.586
It's a secret basement.

04:54.586 --> 04:57.589
♪

04:59.174 --> 05:02.219
[stairs creaking]

05:24.241 --> 05:26.243
[fire crackling]

05:26.243 --> 05:28.036
[inaudible]

05:29.329 --> 05:30.622
[rattling]

05:31.623 --> 05:32.749
[click, buzzing]

05:36.587 --> 05:38.589
SHADOW MAN [distorted]:
Going somewhere, Doctor?

05:39.548 --> 05:42.426
♪

05:43.594 --> 05:44.887
Who is it?

05:57.858 --> 05:58.567
[thud]

05:59.193 --> 06:00.611
- Mr. Munder is going to use the crystal

06:00.611 --> 06:02.821
to transfer his brother's
consciousness to Frank's body.

06:02.821 --> 06:03.739
Just like Project Midnight.

06:03.739 --> 06:05.282
- Burelli said there's
no vessel strong enough.

06:05.282 --> 06:06.950
- Frank will be strong enough.

06:06.950 --> 06:09.036
- Because of The Eye.

06:09.036 --> 06:11.163
Guys, the vessel is the power.

06:12.998 --> 06:14.458
Frank got taken because of me.

06:15.542 --> 06:16.502
- Joe, it's not your fault.

06:16.502 --> 06:18.337
Mr. Munder would have found out
about Frank eventually.

06:18.337 --> 06:20.631
Just look at the extremes
he went through to pull this all off.

06:20.631 --> 06:23.675
But just think. Coming here that night,
you've ruined his original plan.

06:23.675 --> 06:25.969
- He can't use his creepy
secret basement anymore.

06:25.969 --> 06:27.262
- He's improvising. He's on the run.

06:28.180 --> 06:30.098
- So there's still time to save Frank.

06:30.766 --> 06:31.767
If we can find him.

06:31.767 --> 06:34.770
♪

06:36.688 --> 06:39.024
FRANK:
What happened? What am I doing here?

06:39.024 --> 06:40.651
You're in a lot of trouble, Frank.

06:40.651 --> 06:42.861
- Wait. Did you just close
the door to the secret room?

06:42.861 --> 06:45.030
You can't do that!
We're going to be trapped!

06:45.030 --> 06:46.782
- You're already trapped, Frank.

06:46.782 --> 06:48.158
You don't believe me?

06:48.742 --> 06:49.993
Just try to get out of that chair.

06:50.911 --> 06:52.746
[struggling]

06:52.746 --> 06:54.206
- What's happening?

06:54.206 --> 06:56.625
- You're confused.
You need to focus.

06:58.085 --> 06:59.461
You need to wake up!

06:59.461 --> 07:01.672
[echoing]: Wake up!

07:02.965 --> 07:05.133
- Wake up. Wake up, Mr. Hardy.
[gasping]

07:05.133 --> 07:08.011
Welcome to Project Midnight.

07:08.011 --> 07:09.721
[gasping]

07:09.721 --> 07:11.890
[struggling]

07:14.434 --> 07:17.437
♪ theme song ♪

07:27.948 --> 07:30.576
RADIO HOST: Former Dixon City
police officer Fenton Hardy

07:30.576 --> 07:32.244
is wanted for questioning in connection

07:32.244 --> 07:33.954
with multiple homicides in the area.

07:33.954 --> 07:35.622
Hardy was last seen at the Grand Hotel

07:35.622 --> 07:37.040
where he evaded police...
- Hey!

07:37.040 --> 07:38.292
[gasps]
[door shuts]

07:38.292 --> 07:41.211
TRUDY: Hey, are you okay?
- Yeah. Thanks for coming.

07:41.211 --> 07:43.505
- Thanks for coming?
Fenton, you gotta turn yourself in.

07:43.505 --> 07:45.674
- Not till I track down Olivia Kowalski.

07:45.674 --> 07:46.758
Do you have my files?

07:46.758 --> 07:48.385
- Yeah, they're in the back.

07:48.760 --> 07:50.596
- Okay. [grunts]

07:51.889 --> 07:54.808
TRUDY: Okay, what's the plan?
[sighs]

07:54.808 --> 07:56.768
- We're gonna find the woman
who's framing me.

07:56.768 --> 07:57.769
She killed McFarlane,

07:57.769 --> 07:59.563
and then she killed another guy
in a vacant building.

07:59.563 --> 08:01.940
Then she killed another guy
and dumped his body in my hotel room.

08:01.940 --> 08:03.775
And I recognize him from these files.

08:05.444 --> 08:06.987
Both those other guys that she killed

08:06.987 --> 08:08.822
were each hired
to guard vacant buildings

08:08.822 --> 08:11.033
owned by George Estabrook Enterprises.

08:11.033 --> 08:14.828
So, why would Stratemeyer Global
be guarding empty old buildings?

08:15.746 --> 08:18.248
- Maybe they're not so empty.
- Right?

08:18.248 --> 08:20.334
Olivia stole a codex
from one of the buildings.

08:20.334 --> 08:23.045
Willing to bet she's looking
for a second codex now.

08:23.045 --> 08:25.088
- What's in the codex?
- Scrolls.

08:25.088 --> 08:28.467
She tried to get McFarlane's scroll,
but he died protecting it, gave it to me.

08:29.676 --> 08:31.970
And that scroll has got
ripped edges on two sides.

08:31.970 --> 08:33.931
Makes me think that all the scrolls

08:33.931 --> 08:35.557
are part of a larger document.

08:35.557 --> 08:36.850
- So she's collecting them.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.769
- Yeah. Got a feeling
we're going to find her

08:38.769 --> 08:40.896
in an empty old building owned by...

08:40.896 --> 08:43.482
- George Estabrook Enterprises.

08:44.233 --> 08:46.235
We got to get there first.
- Yep.

08:46.985 --> 08:48.445
[Trudy sighs]

08:48.445 --> 08:50.322
[keys jingling, starts engine]

08:50.322 --> 08:53.325
♪

08:56.745 --> 08:59.122
CHET: If you're looking for Frank,
he's not here.

09:00.582 --> 09:03.001
- But he was. Where is he now?

09:03.001 --> 09:04.711
- Hoping you could tell us.

09:04.711 --> 09:05.879
- Don't tell me you lost him.

09:05.879 --> 09:08.841
- Oh no, we'll find him just as soon as
you give us that check.

09:09.550 --> 09:10.759
- And why would I do that?

09:10.759 --> 09:13.595
- Because you're out of options.
You made your play,

09:13.595 --> 09:15.848
you lost.
- Game's not over yet.

09:15.848 --> 09:16.890
- [scoff] Sure it is.

09:16.890 --> 09:18.475
Tell me, how are your bosses
at Stratemeyer Global

09:18.475 --> 09:22.062
going to feel about you going rogue
and killing one of their own?

09:22.062 --> 09:24.940
- They're going to find out what happens
to people when they cross me.

09:24.940 --> 09:28.235
- You gonna kill us
like you killed Mack?

09:28.235 --> 09:30.279
-'Cause I don't think all of us
gonna fit in that bathtub.

09:30.279 --> 09:33.240
- Mack outlived his usefulness to me,

09:33.240 --> 09:35.576
so I helped him stay relevant.

09:37.369 --> 09:39.621
And, yes, that was a threat.

09:39.621 --> 09:42.332
But if you're trying to get me
to confess on that hidden camera,

09:42.332 --> 09:43.750
it won't work.

09:43.750 --> 09:45.794
I disabled the feed,

09:45.794 --> 09:48.422
just like you killed my listening device.

09:48.422 --> 09:52.134
- About that. I have a friend whose dad
owns an electronics shop, so I went

09:52.134 --> 09:54.386
and made some modifications to that bug.

09:54.386 --> 09:57.598
It's a whole lot cooler now because...

09:57.598 --> 09:58.640
it's way more portable.

09:58.640 --> 10:01.310
♪

10:01.310 --> 10:03.812
You guys get all that?
- Loud and clear.

10:05.230 --> 10:06.648
RILEY [on radio]: Move in.

10:06.648 --> 10:08.400
- I never admitted anything.

10:08.400 --> 10:11.904
The motel room is still under JB Cox,
and your little recording is illegal.

10:12.487 --> 10:15.282
- That's okay.
The recording was just a bonus.

10:15.282 --> 10:17.701
- Yeah because, apparently,
Mack's killer was dumb enough

10:17.701 --> 10:19.870
to leave her gun in the room
she shot him in.

10:19.870 --> 10:22.873
[police radio chatter]

10:23.624 --> 10:26.001
[handcuffs clicking]

10:27.294 --> 10:29.296
- This isn't over.

10:31.507 --> 10:33.717
[Chet sighs]

10:33.717 --> 10:35.302
[tracker beeping]

10:35.302 --> 10:37.804
CHET: Frank!
BELINDA: He's having a vision right now?

10:37.804 --> 10:40.933
- You're not gonna believe where he is.
Come on. Let's go tell the others.

10:40.933 --> 10:42.392
[high-pitched tone]

10:42.392 --> 10:44.853
- Ah! Ah!

10:44.853 --> 10:46.605
[tone continues]
[groans]

10:47.606 --> 10:50.192
[Frank groaning]

10:50.192 --> 10:51.902
[gasping]

10:53.278 --> 10:55.197
[thud, tone stops]
[Frank gasps]

10:55.197 --> 10:58.200
♪

10:58.992 --> 11:00.786
- You know I've been in here before.

11:00.786 --> 11:03.247
[switches clicking]
I know about Project Midnight.

11:04.498 --> 11:06.708
I saw your photo in the yearbook.
I know what they did to you.

11:06.708 --> 11:08.418
- You don't know anything.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.629
[beep]
- Then help me understand!

11:10.629 --> 11:13.090
[beeping]
Why am I here?

11:14.466 --> 11:17.261
Why did you steal the crystal?
How does it help you get revenge?

11:19.096 --> 11:22.850
- Is that what you think this is all for?
Revenge.

11:24.059 --> 11:26.478
I can see why
your young mind would go there.

11:26.478 --> 11:28.480
That was my first instinct, too.
[pressing buttons, beeping]

11:29.648 --> 11:31.191
But, this...

11:32.609 --> 11:34.194
is so much more.

11:36.613 --> 11:39.533
Desire for vengeance

11:39.533 --> 11:42.786
is a fleeting emotion based in anger

11:42.786 --> 11:45.998
and hurt. Anger and hurt...
[Frank gasps]

11:45.998 --> 11:48.000
can heal with time.

11:49.543 --> 11:52.254
But do you know what stays with you

11:52.254 --> 11:54.256
no matter what, Frank?

11:55.215 --> 11:57.718
What persists through time?

11:59.428 --> 12:00.679
Love.

12:01.513 --> 12:02.848
Love. Love never ends.

12:02.848 --> 12:05.309
Aching, painful, mournful love

12:05.309 --> 12:07.019
that comes with missing someone so much

12:07.019 --> 12:10.022
that you would do anything
to bring them back.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.108
Can you understand that?

12:13.108 --> 12:15.527
♪

12:15.527 --> 12:17.029
- More than anything.

12:20.574 --> 12:23.577
- Project Midnight
took my brother from me.

12:25.662 --> 12:27.956
I'm not going to avenge him.
I'm going to save him.

12:28.665 --> 12:30.167
- Your brother.

12:31.919 --> 12:34.505
Your twin brother. What was his name?

12:34.505 --> 12:37.299
- Don't you speak of him
in the past tense!

12:38.050 --> 12:39.885
His name is Aaron.

12:39.885 --> 12:42.095
- You said that--
- He's in the crystal.

12:43.555 --> 12:45.474
That's what it's for. It's a way-station.

12:45.474 --> 12:47.768
Aaron's body is in the hospital,

12:47.768 --> 12:50.270
but his consciousness is in the crystal.

12:51.980 --> 12:53.315
That's what Project Midnight was.

12:53.315 --> 12:56.193
A way to transfer a person's consciousness

12:56.193 --> 12:58.278
into the body of another. It's actually...

12:58.278 --> 13:00.781
It's quite a remarkable idea,
but the project failed,

13:00.781 --> 13:03.742
and Aaron became trapped.

13:03.742 --> 13:07.162
His body rendered nothing more
than a catatonic husk, but my brother

13:07.162 --> 13:10.374
is alive, Mr. Hardy. In here.

13:11.458 --> 13:13.919
- So, what do you need me for?

13:13.919 --> 13:16.797
Why not put Aaron's
consciousness in Aaron's body?

13:18.048 --> 13:19.550
- That was the original plan.

13:21.635 --> 13:25.138
I had my brother in the chair
in my basement.

13:25.138 --> 13:27.140
I had my hand on the lever.

13:27.140 --> 13:29.685
I had everything I wanted,
everything I worked for...

13:29.685 --> 13:31.770
♪

13:31.770 --> 13:33.730
and then something stopped me.

13:34.857 --> 13:36.275
- What was it?

13:37.025 --> 13:40.279
- Imagine standing on the brink
of getting exactly

13:40.279 --> 13:42.155
what you want most
in the world, Mr. Hardy.

13:42.698 --> 13:44.575
Now, picture it slipping away.

13:46.118 --> 13:48.537
Aaron's body failed once,
I couldn't risk it failing again.

13:48.537 --> 13:51.290
So, I changed my plan.

13:51.290 --> 13:52.708
I needed a test run.

13:52.708 --> 13:54.042
- Dennis.

13:54.042 --> 13:56.503
- Dennis was in the wrong place
at the wrong time,

13:56.503 --> 13:58.547
and when he started to remember,
I helped him forget.

13:59.339 --> 14:02.593
But you, Mr. Hardy, are exactly
where you're supposed to be.

14:03.427 --> 14:04.761
Let's proceed, shall we?

14:04.761 --> 14:06.096
[grunts]

14:06.096 --> 14:09.600
[rain pattering]

14:09.600 --> 14:11.435
♪

14:22.696 --> 14:25.199
FENTON: Fancy meeting you here.
[scoffs]

14:26.533 --> 14:28.118
- Your resilience is impressive.

14:28.118 --> 14:29.620
Thank you.

14:29.620 --> 14:32.122
- Breaking the law
to come after me.

14:32.623 --> 14:33.749
Didn't think you had it in you.

14:34.291 --> 14:37.169
But you shouldn't have come alone.
- You neither.

14:37.169 --> 14:39.880
[thump]
Oh! What are you doing?

14:41.673 --> 14:43.926
- She was going for the gun!
- No, she wasn't!

14:43.926 --> 14:45.761
- Well, it-it looked like she was!

14:46.345 --> 14:48.222
- How am I supposed to question her now?

14:48.222 --> 14:49.431
You are so impulsive!

14:49.431 --> 14:51.600
- Oh, that's rich coming from you.
I just saved your life!

14:51.600 --> 14:53.393
- Will you please just
put that thing down?

14:56.063 --> 14:57.523
[sighs]
[brick clatters]

14:57.523 --> 14:58.857
Your adventuring days are over.

14:59.650 --> 15:01.401
- Are you serious?
- Yep.

15:01.401 --> 15:03.570
- You're still in a lot of trouble, pal.

15:03.570 --> 15:05.405
- That is exactly why I need you to go.

15:05.405 --> 15:07.407
I can't have you more involved
than you already are.

15:07.407 --> 15:09.868
Plus, you're kind of a liability.

15:09.868 --> 15:12.454
- No. I got caught up in the heat
of the moment.

15:12.454 --> 15:13.872
I can reign it in.

15:13.872 --> 15:14.915
- Yeah, you do that.

15:15.916 --> 15:16.667
At home.

15:17.459 --> 15:18.669
Take these.

15:20.087 --> 15:22.464
Keep them safe.
Don't tell anyone.

15:22.464 --> 15:25.467
[rain continues]

15:28.804 --> 15:30.097
- What are you gonna do with her?

15:31.557 --> 15:34.059
- I'm gonna wait till she comes to,
and then I'm gonna question her.

15:34.059 --> 15:37.062
♪

15:42.401 --> 15:44.611
- You know, in some ways,
Bridgeport really is

15:44.611 --> 15:46.697
the perfect place to pull this off.

15:46.697 --> 15:47.948
♪

15:47.948 --> 15:50.868
Everyone here is so preoccupied

15:50.868 --> 15:53.829
with the lore of Demon Day and Demon's Paw

15:53.829 --> 15:56.123
and demon blah, blah, blah.
But no one seems to remember

15:56.123 --> 15:58.417
the real threats walking among them.

16:00.544 --> 16:02.087
- You.

16:04.631 --> 16:06.175
[chair rattling]

16:07.092 --> 16:08.594
- You think I'm the demon here?

16:09.553 --> 16:11.054
Mr. Hardy, I'm the victim.

16:12.347 --> 16:13.849
I'm the one triumphing over people

16:13.849 --> 16:16.643
like Gloria Estabrook and Dr. Burelli

16:16.643 --> 16:19.563
and The Circle of The Eye
and Stratemeyer Global.

16:19.563 --> 16:23.025
Maybe you should reconsider
which side you're aligned with,

16:23.025 --> 16:26.612
Mr. Hardy. The man moving
mountains to save his brother,

16:26.612 --> 16:28.280
or the powerful people and institutions

16:28.280 --> 16:31.116
that used and experimented on teenagers,

16:31.116 --> 16:32.701
and then covered it up!

16:33.744 --> 16:35.204
- You did the same thing.

16:35.204 --> 16:36.705
- Did I?

16:37.414 --> 16:40.209
Please enlighten me.
- You used Vanessa and Lola.

16:40.209 --> 16:42.753
- They could have said no,
and I could have found someone else.

16:42.753 --> 16:43.921
- You could have done it yourself!

16:43.921 --> 16:47.049
- What would that have gotten me, Frank?

16:47.049 --> 16:48.509
Hm?

16:48.509 --> 16:50.886
Caught. On Demon Day.

16:50.886 --> 16:53.680
That's what.
- All that time.

16:53.680 --> 16:55.682
All that planning.
And then Dennis.

16:55.682 --> 16:58.685
♪

16:58.685 --> 17:00.604
Why not just kill Dennis?

17:01.730 --> 17:03.232
- Kill Dennis.

17:04.775 --> 17:06.401
Have you ever taken a life, Frank?

17:11.615 --> 17:14.284
I think not. I'm not a monster.

17:18.580 --> 17:19.998
- You killed Burelli.

17:19.998 --> 17:22.209
- Burelli had to die
because she knew who I was,

17:22.209 --> 17:24.670
and she was going to ruin my plan.

17:24.670 --> 17:26.672
But for Dennis, there was another way.

17:27.673 --> 17:29.883
I used the machine
to wipe away his memories,

17:29.883 --> 17:31.093
take him off the game board,

17:31.093 --> 17:33.595
but it wasn't the full Midnight treatment.

17:36.014 --> 17:37.724
Dennis will recover.

17:37.724 --> 17:40.811
He may even get all of
his memories back. Eventually.

17:40.811 --> 17:43.230
I just needed to buy myself time

17:43.230 --> 17:45.399
to get the crystal.
No one was ever supposed to know.

17:45.399 --> 17:48.986
But then, you and your brother
and your friends kept...

17:48.986 --> 17:51.572
pressing! And I had to react.

17:51.572 --> 17:54.575
I had to improvise.
I had to advance my timeline.

17:54.575 --> 17:58.161
And it's a good thing I did.
Otherwise, I never would have found out

17:58.161 --> 17:59.746
about you.

17:59.746 --> 18:02.040
And the power of The Eye.

18:02.040 --> 18:03.709
- You know about The Eye?

18:04.793 --> 18:05.836
- Thanks to your brother.

18:07.171 --> 18:09.423
The irony. Here I was,
on the verge of being caught,

18:09.423 --> 18:12.634
Joe and his friends nipping at my heels,
and instead, fate intervenes

18:12.634 --> 18:14.928
and delivers you to me.

18:14.928 --> 18:18.015
♪

18:18.015 --> 18:20.017
- The vessel is the power.
- That's right.

18:21.101 --> 18:24.104
You're the only one strong enough
to handle the transfer, Mr. Hardy.

18:26.481 --> 18:28.483
- You can't be sure
that's what that means!

18:28.483 --> 18:30.986
- Why else would Gloria Estabrook
write it on that scroll?

18:32.779 --> 18:34.364
- How do you know Gloria's
the one that wrote it?

18:34.364 --> 18:36.742
- She's the one behind Project Midnight.
It's her crystal.

18:37.618 --> 18:39.036
- You're not as smart as you think.

18:39.036 --> 18:41.663
- And what are you implying, Mr. Hardy?

18:41.663 --> 18:43.916
That I didn't do my homework?
That I didn't think it through?

18:43.916 --> 18:45.918
- You over-thought it.

18:45.918 --> 18:47.461
All the framing.

18:47.461 --> 18:50.047
All the people involved.
All the variables.

18:51.381 --> 18:52.883
You overcomplicated it.

18:52.883 --> 18:56.220
- Complicated ideas
require complex planning!

18:56.220 --> 18:57.679
Like writing computer code.

18:57.679 --> 19:00.015
"If this, then that."
"If that, then this."

19:00.015 --> 19:02.142
"If then." "If then."

19:02.142 --> 19:05.604
Every plan needs a contingency!
Every contingency needs a failsafe!

19:05.604 --> 19:08.440
I never planned to kidnap Dennis
or kill Burelli

19:08.440 --> 19:10.526
or swap places with my brother!

19:10.526 --> 19:13.570
I never planned to kidnap you,
but I had to!

19:13.570 --> 19:17.032
Because the transfer requires The Eye!

19:17.032 --> 19:19.743
The power of The Eye!
The Circle of The Eye!

19:19.743 --> 19:21.078
It's always been a part of this!

19:21.078 --> 19:23.205
Even when it was just
a rumor at Rosegrave!

19:23.205 --> 19:25.707
I never cared about it, but Aaron did!

19:25.707 --> 19:28.335
♪

19:28.335 --> 19:30.003
I couldn't stop him.

19:30.003 --> 19:32.256
YOUNG ADRIAN:
Aaron! Aaron, wait!

19:32.256 --> 19:33.924
AARON: You shouldn't have
followed me here, Adrian.

19:33.924 --> 19:35.926
YOUNG ADRIAN: You signed up
for Project Midnight, didn't you?

19:35.926 --> 19:37.970
I thought you were joining
the Latin Club with me.

19:37.970 --> 19:40.097
- To study some dead language?
What's the point?

19:40.097 --> 19:41.807
- That's better than being a guinea pig.

19:42.641 --> 19:44.101
- You don't get it.

19:44.852 --> 19:46.728
They're going to let me join
The Circle of The Eye.

19:47.354 --> 19:49.022
- The Circle's a myth.

19:49.398 --> 19:51.400
- [scoffs] It's not.

19:51.984 --> 19:53.026
It's real.

19:54.111 --> 19:57.489
If I'm in The Circle, do you know
what that means for both of us?

19:58.574 --> 20:00.075
We can have anything we want.

20:01.076 --> 20:02.828
- They're just using you.

20:04.705 --> 20:05.747
- I'm doing this.

20:14.965 --> 20:16.133
[door shuts]

20:17.718 --> 20:19.511
BURELLI:
Patient B is ready, Nurse Cody.

20:19.511 --> 20:22.514
♪

20:23.682 --> 20:24.766
[buzz, blip]

20:25.267 --> 20:28.187
[low whirring]
[clicking]

20:28.187 --> 20:31.273
AUTOMATED VOICE: 100. 93.
[alarm blaring]

20:31.273 --> 20:35.402
86. 79. 72.
[high-pitched whirring]

20:35.402 --> 20:38.322
[rumbling]
65. 58.

20:38.322 --> 20:40.782
YOUNG ADRIAN: No! Stop! Turn it off! No!
AUTOMATED VOICE: 51.

20:40.782 --> 20:42.576
- You can't do this!
AUTOMATED VOICE: 44.

20:42.576 --> 20:44.119
37.
- Get him outta here!

20:44.119 --> 20:44.953
[beeping]

20:44.953 --> 20:47.414
AUTOMATED VOICE: 30. 23.
- Ah! Stop! Aaron!

20:47.414 --> 20:48.832
Ah!

20:48.832 --> 20:51.960
AUTOMATED VOICE: 16. 9.
[beeping, whirring]

20:56.798 --> 20:59.801
[Burelli breathing heavily]

20:59.801 --> 21:02.804
♪

21:02.804 --> 21:04.306
- Is he dead?

21:05.891 --> 21:08.185
- Not dead. No.

21:10.229 --> 21:12.022
But your brother,
as you knew him is gone.

21:12.022 --> 21:13.982
[heavy breathing]

21:13.982 --> 21:16.693
He'll be taken to a facility,
Pine Grove Institute.

21:16.693 --> 21:19.154
He'll be... well taken care of there.

21:20.364 --> 21:21.990
But you can't visit him, Adrian.

21:22.491 --> 21:23.992
You need to disappear.

21:25.494 --> 21:27.663
The powers that be are paying
for my silence.

21:27.663 --> 21:29.081
I'm willing to pay for yours.

21:30.290 --> 21:32.376
- Wouldn't it be easier
just to kill me?

21:32.876 --> 21:35.629
- For them... Yes.

21:36.755 --> 21:40.467
But I'm a doctor, Adrian.
I don't intend to harm.

21:40.467 --> 21:42.135
This was an accident.

21:42.135 --> 21:43.679
Your brother knew the risks.

21:44.304 --> 21:45.889
- No, he didn't.

21:46.890 --> 21:49.226
- Take the money
and forget this ever happened.

21:50.644 --> 21:53.021
Your life will be better for it.

21:53.021 --> 21:55.023
I promise you.

21:55.023 --> 21:58.026
♪

22:05.450 --> 22:06.743
FRANK:
Please.

22:06.743 --> 22:08.328
I have a brother.

22:09.913 --> 22:12.749
I am a brother.
You can't do this to me.

22:12.749 --> 22:14.251
- I have to.

22:16.170 --> 22:17.588
It has to be you, Frank.

22:17.588 --> 22:19.256
[click, buzz]

22:19.256 --> 22:21.508
I need to download you into the crystal.
[whirring]

22:21.508 --> 22:24.970
Because of the power of The Eye,
you're the only one whose body and mind

22:24.970 --> 22:26.471
can handle the transfer.

22:27.389 --> 22:30.058
The only one who can serve
as a vessel for Aaron's consciousness.

22:31.351 --> 22:34.021
And this is my chance to save my brother.

22:34.021 --> 22:35.856
You're his only way out.

22:39.276 --> 22:40.319
It's time.

22:40.319 --> 22:41.361
Oh!

22:42.237 --> 22:43.614
Ow...

22:43.614 --> 22:44.948
Ow!

22:44.948 --> 22:46.658
[yells]
[Frank grunts]

22:46.658 --> 22:49.119
[gasping]

22:50.370 --> 22:51.371
[whimpers]

22:53.081 --> 22:56.084
- You can't do this. No!
AUTOMATED VOICE: 100. 93.

22:56.084 --> 22:59.838
[machine whirring]
86. 79.

22:59.838 --> 23:02.508
[gasps, yells]
72.

23:02.508 --> 23:06.303
65. 58. 51.
FRANK: [whimpers] No, no, no!

23:07.262 --> 23:11.099
AUTOMATED VOICE: 44. 37.
[beeping, whirring]

23:11.099 --> 23:13.727
30. 23.
[high-pitched whirring]

23:13.727 --> 23:15.896
16.

23:15.896 --> 23:18.065
9. 2.

23:18.065 --> 23:19.858
[beeping]

23:19.858 --> 23:22.861
[whirring down]

23:22.861 --> 23:25.531
[alarm sounding quietly]

23:27.533 --> 23:28.534
[gasps]

23:28.534 --> 23:31.537
♪

23:31.537 --> 23:34.540
[clock ticking]

23:41.880 --> 23:43.131
- Is this another vision?

23:43.131 --> 23:46.051
- No, Frank. It's the crystal.

23:46.051 --> 23:48.220
- Why does it look like
my Grandma's house?

23:48.929 --> 23:51.265
- This isn't Gloria's house, Frank.

23:51.265 --> 23:54.142
[footsteps]
Listen.

23:55.102 --> 23:56.186
GEORGE:
Wait there.

23:57.813 --> 24:00.774
- It's The Circle, isn't it? Let me help.

24:00.774 --> 24:03.986
- Gloria, I will always love you,

24:03.986 --> 24:06.822
but you will never be part
of The Circle of The Eye.

24:06.822 --> 24:09.366
I know one day, you'll understand.

24:09.867 --> 24:11.869
And I hope you'll forgive me.

24:13.245 --> 24:14.746
Goodbye, Gloria.

24:15.581 --> 24:18.625
- Father, just stay
and explain your plan to me.

24:18.625 --> 24:20.586
Trust me!
GEORGE: I do trust you.

24:21.378 --> 24:22.963
But I can't tell you everything right now.

24:22.963 --> 24:25.299
If I do, my plan won't work.

24:25.299 --> 24:28.468
There is one thing you need
to know before I go.

24:28.468 --> 24:30.804
A package will be coming for you from me.

24:30.804 --> 24:34.183
You must follow
my instructions explicitly.

24:34.183 --> 24:37.811
Whatever happens,
you must trust me. Tell no one.

24:37.811 --> 24:41.273
And always remember
what must happen at midnight.

24:41.815 --> 24:43.358
- [sighs] What are you saying?

24:43.358 --> 24:45.527
What happens at midnight?

24:45.527 --> 24:47.487
- If I tell you now,

24:47.487 --> 24:49.031
it won't happen at all.

24:49.031 --> 24:50.115
- I don't understand.

24:50.115 --> 24:53.368
- But you will. And I will see you again.

24:53.994 --> 24:55.078
I promise.

24:55.579 --> 24:58.207
Goodbye, my dear daughter.

24:58.207 --> 25:00.751
♪

25:01.668 --> 25:03.212
- Why are you showing me this?

25:03.212 --> 25:05.756
- Patience, Frank. You'll see.

25:12.513 --> 25:15.349
- What is all this?
- Memories. Hopes.

25:15.349 --> 25:18.393
Glimpses of the path towards
getting what one wants the most.

25:18.393 --> 25:21.396
[clock ticking]

25:25.609 --> 25:26.902
Too late, Frank.

25:28.111 --> 25:29.947
♪

25:41.208 --> 25:44.211
[warbling]
- Stop! Okay, we're wasting time!

25:45.128 --> 25:47.923
We need to find Aaron
and stop the transfer.

25:47.923 --> 25:51.218
What Munder's doing has nothing
to do with my great-grandfather.

25:51.218 --> 25:54.304
- It has everything to do
with George Estabrook.

25:54.304 --> 25:55.973
It always has.

25:55.973 --> 25:58.976
♪ soft music playing ♪

26:08.151 --> 26:10.153
♪ soft music fades out ♪

26:16.410 --> 26:19.746
- I'm trying to understand.
The crystal, it stores consciousness?

26:20.247 --> 26:22.708
- Yes, it can,

26:22.708 --> 26:24.835
but it's more of a way-station.

26:24.835 --> 26:27.296
The transfer in is fairly simple.

26:27.296 --> 26:30.215
Getting out has always been...
the tricky part.

26:31.008 --> 26:33.635
- Where's Aaron Munder?
- Not here.

26:33.635 --> 26:34.761
Not anymore.

26:35.762 --> 26:37.139
- Anymore?

26:38.098 --> 26:39.474
His brother thinks--
- His brother thinks

26:39.474 --> 26:41.602
exactly what he's meant to think.

26:41.602 --> 26:43.520
Munder's plan will fail

26:43.520 --> 26:45.230
to serve a higher purpose.

26:45.689 --> 26:47.149
- What purpose?

26:47.149 --> 26:49.151
- Our time is done together, Frank.

26:50.068 --> 26:53.363
The Eye's loyalty has always been
with its original master.

26:53.363 --> 26:56.366
♪

26:59.494 --> 27:01.121
I've been picturing this moment, Francis.

27:02.831 --> 27:05.459
I always wanted to meet my great-grandson

27:05.459 --> 27:09.004
ever since that day
we saw each other on the beach.

27:10.297 --> 27:13.300
- You didn't die when your plane
crashed into the ocean.

27:15.344 --> 27:17.221
You were never on it.
- No.

27:18.055 --> 27:19.932
But my piece of the relic was.

27:19.932 --> 27:22.935
I needed to be here to wait for you.

27:24.520 --> 27:27.189
What are you, 22?

27:27.189 --> 27:28.857
23?

27:28.857 --> 27:31.193
- I'm 16.
- 16.

27:32.361 --> 27:36.114
My goodness.
Time moves so differently here.

27:36.114 --> 27:37.157
You'll get used to it.

27:37.157 --> 27:39.284
[rattling, rumbling]

27:39.284 --> 27:42.287
♪

27:43.372 --> 27:44.581
- What's happening?

27:45.666 --> 27:47.668
- The transfer is about to begin.

27:48.752 --> 27:50.003
And then, I'll be free.

27:51.505 --> 27:52.714
The Eye

27:52.714 --> 27:54.925
has shown me the path, Francis.

27:54.925 --> 27:56.760
This is all part of it.

27:57.594 --> 27:59.304
I truly wish there was another way.

27:59.304 --> 28:00.973
- I'm going to stop you.

28:01.849 --> 28:03.392
- Impossible.

28:03.392 --> 28:06.144
Once I step into the light,
I'll return to the real world.

28:08.772 --> 28:11.775
♪

28:11.775 --> 28:14.778
♪ rock music playing ♪

28:19.908 --> 28:22.911
[machine powering up]

28:24.079 --> 28:26.123
[beeping]

28:28.458 --> 28:29.459
[bang]

28:29.459 --> 28:32.462
♪ music continues ♪

28:35.340 --> 28:36.341
[door slams]

28:43.348 --> 28:46.351
♪

28:50.939 --> 28:53.942
♪

28:59.364 --> 29:01.200
[chandelier jingling]

29:03.243 --> 29:04.411
[shouting, grunts]

29:07.456 --> 29:10.459
[muffled alarm blaring]

29:18.342 --> 29:19.259
[muffled thud]

29:22.429 --> 29:23.472
[muffled thud]

29:24.598 --> 29:25.933
[muffled punch]

29:25.933 --> 29:28.936
♪

29:28.936 --> 29:31.772
[beeping]

29:31.772 --> 29:34.525
[high-pitched whirring]

29:35.150 --> 29:37.402
[groaning]

29:37.945 --> 29:39.655
- No!

29:39.655 --> 29:42.241
[high-pitched whirring]

29:42.241 --> 29:42.950
GEORGE:
No...

29:44.451 --> 29:48.080
[chandelier jingling]
[grunting]

29:49.414 --> 29:50.707
[grunts]

29:50.707 --> 29:52.417
[whirring]

29:52.417 --> 29:54.419
[inaudible]

29:54.419 --> 29:56.547
[yelling]

29:58.674 --> 30:00.425
♪

30:00.425 --> 30:02.761
[jingling]

30:05.305 --> 30:08.308
[explosion]

30:08.308 --> 30:10.727
♪

30:10.727 --> 30:12.145
[muffled thudding]

30:17.317 --> 30:19.653
[buzzing]
[quiet whirring]

30:27.828 --> 30:30.831
[heavy breathing]

30:31.957 --> 30:33.375
- Aaron?

30:33.917 --> 30:35.502
Aaron?

30:35.502 --> 30:37.004
- Adrian.

30:37.671 --> 30:38.714
You came for me.

30:39.339 --> 30:40.340
[gasps]

30:41.800 --> 30:42.801
[gasps]

30:42.801 --> 30:45.220
[heavy breathing]
Get me out of this.

30:45.220 --> 30:47.222
Come on. Come on.

30:48.473 --> 30:50.017
Come on. [laughs]

30:52.311 --> 30:54.855
[gasping]
Come on. Come on, Aaron.

30:55.814 --> 30:56.899
It's okay.

30:56.899 --> 30:59.401
It's okay, Aaron! Come on!

30:59.401 --> 31:01.236
Come on. We're almost there.

31:01.236 --> 31:03.572
[panting]
Aaron.

31:05.532 --> 31:06.533
[gasps]

31:09.077 --> 31:10.329
What is it?

31:12.122 --> 31:13.540
Come on, we need to go.
Come on, Aaron--

31:13.540 --> 31:15.375
- I'm not Aaron.

31:15.375 --> 31:17.586
♪

31:17.586 --> 31:19.254
Your brother wasn't in that crystal.

31:20.672 --> 31:22.716
He was just a pawn in a very long game.

31:24.009 --> 31:25.302
So are you.

31:26.053 --> 31:27.638
- No.

31:27.638 --> 31:30.098
- I'm so sorry for what happened
to you and your brother.

31:30.098 --> 31:32.392
- No. The transfer worked. I saw it work.

31:32.392 --> 31:36.188
You're just confused.
My-my plan was perfect.

31:36.188 --> 31:39.775
All the errors were accounted for.
You're just confused, Aaron!

31:40.651 --> 31:42.694
- Look into my eyes, Adrian.

31:44.029 --> 31:45.864
What do you see?

31:47.407 --> 31:48.909
Do you see your brother?

31:50.827 --> 31:53.330
Do you see someone who loves you?

31:55.165 --> 31:58.168
♪

32:03.131 --> 32:06.635
- Hey! Hey! Hey!
Get off him! Get off of him!

32:06.635 --> 32:08.178
[panting]

32:08.178 --> 32:11.181
[high-pitched whirring]

32:11.181 --> 32:14.184
[handcuffs clicking]
[Frank coughing]

32:17.271 --> 32:20.315
[gagging]
- Frank?

32:21.024 --> 32:22.025
[coughs]

32:22.985 --> 32:25.028
PHIL:
Are you okay?

32:25.028 --> 32:28.031
[high-pitched whirring continues]

32:28.031 --> 32:30.033
[grunting]
CALLIE: It's okay. It's over now.

32:31.285 --> 32:32.286
Frank?

32:37.666 --> 32:39.668
[whirring stops]

32:44.047 --> 32:45.465
- Stop!

32:50.762 --> 32:52.598
- Give up the power.

32:53.765 --> 32:55.517
- Now?

32:56.310 --> 32:57.978
- Before it's too late.

32:58.729 --> 33:01.356
You swore on Mom's grave.

33:01.356 --> 33:04.359
♪

33:06.820 --> 33:09.156
- If I give up the power,

33:09.156 --> 33:11.366
I won't get what I want most.

33:11.825 --> 33:13.827
- We'll still have The Eye.

33:13.827 --> 33:15.454
We can still use the power.

33:15.454 --> 33:17.414
It'll just be back where it belongs.

33:17.414 --> 33:19.082
Not in you.

33:20.042 --> 33:22.794
Do it. Now.

33:23.795 --> 33:24.796
[sighs]

33:34.348 --> 33:37.351
[relic humming]

33:37.351 --> 33:40.354
[whirring]

33:42.439 --> 33:45.484
[humming, whirring continue]

33:47.152 --> 33:48.195
[noises stop]

33:49.905 --> 33:51.323
[sighs]

33:51.323 --> 33:53.575
[lights buzzing]

33:53.575 --> 33:54.868
See, guys?

33:54.868 --> 33:56.870
[sighs] Wasn't so bad.

33:57.162 --> 33:57.871
[thud]

33:59.081 --> 34:02.084
♪

34:04.628 --> 34:06.046
[Olivia grunts]

34:06.046 --> 34:07.464
[sighs]

34:10.342 --> 34:12.636
- Who ordered Laura's death?

34:12.636 --> 34:14.096
[sighs]

34:14.096 --> 34:15.931
Give me their name.

34:16.807 --> 34:18.851
- I don't have it, Fenton.

34:19.351 --> 34:22.354
You were in my way,
and I needed a fall guy.

34:22.354 --> 34:24.231
- So that's it?

34:25.148 --> 34:27.234
[Olivia sighs]
It's all a lie.

34:27.234 --> 34:29.736
- You're already chasing ghosts.

34:29.736 --> 34:31.154
What's one more?

34:32.698 --> 34:33.991
But it wasn't all a lie.

34:33.991 --> 34:35.701
Just the part about Laura.

34:36.952 --> 34:38.871
I have a mission, Fenton.

34:38.871 --> 34:40.372
A noble one.

34:40.873 --> 34:43.125
- Well, I'm gonna take you to the police,

34:43.125 --> 34:45.377
and you're going to have 20-to-life
to think about how noble

34:45.377 --> 34:47.004
your mission is.

34:47.004 --> 34:48.547
All those murders.

34:48.547 --> 34:50.215
Were they worth it?

34:50.215 --> 34:53.218
♪

34:56.388 --> 34:57.556
[gasps]

34:57.556 --> 34:59.725
[TV chatter]

34:59.725 --> 35:02.186
- Hey. Go easy, go easy, go easy.

35:02.853 --> 35:05.147
Everything's okay. Everyone's safe.

35:05.147 --> 35:07.149
So are you.
- Where is it?

35:08.483 --> 35:09.526
The relic.

35:11.486 --> 35:12.988
- I gave it to Belinda's dad.

35:13.989 --> 35:15.782
- What did he do with it?
What if he--

35:15.782 --> 35:17.534
- He won't.

35:17.534 --> 35:18.994
Okay? He'll make sure The Eye

35:18.994 --> 35:20.829
never sees the light of day ever again.

35:22.206 --> 35:24.208
- So you never planned for us to keep it.

35:24.875 --> 35:26.210
You lied to me.

35:27.085 --> 35:29.254
- I did what I had to do.

35:29.254 --> 35:30.756
I had to save you,

35:30.756 --> 35:33.008
from Mr. Munder and from The Eye.

35:34.218 --> 35:35.719
I wanted my brother back.

35:40.015 --> 35:42.100
- Thank you.

35:42.100 --> 35:44.520
♪

35:45.020 --> 35:48.023
- The Circle is everywhere, Fenton.

35:48.023 --> 35:49.942
You need to let me
finish what I started,

35:49.942 --> 35:51.527
or you're going to end up like your wife.

35:52.444 --> 35:53.487
- You leave her out of it.

35:54.196 --> 35:56.990
- I'm trying to prevent something terrible
from happening!

35:58.450 --> 36:01.954
You have no idea how close
you are to losing everything.

36:02.913 --> 36:05.791
My mother tried to warn
your boys last year.

36:05.791 --> 36:08.919
"The ground you walk on is cursed.

36:08.919 --> 36:11.296
"And if you're not careful,

36:11.296 --> 36:13.340
your lives will be, too."

36:14.883 --> 36:17.761
The Eye is only the beginning.

36:17.761 --> 36:19.763
There are more relics out there.

36:19.763 --> 36:22.766
♪

36:22.766 --> 36:24.393
Their powers are great.

36:25.352 --> 36:28.063
But the curse is even greater.

36:29.439 --> 36:31.900
If these relics fall into the wrong hands,

36:32.609 --> 36:36.446
the peril that follows
will be insurmountable.

36:40.117 --> 36:42.077
I've been collecting the codexes
for someone

36:42.077 --> 36:43.829
who won't be corrupted by the relics.

36:43.829 --> 36:46.123
Someone who can protect them.

36:46.123 --> 36:47.207
And all of us.

36:48.083 --> 36:49.501
- I want to meet this person.

36:50.711 --> 36:52.379
- You're not ready for that.

36:52.921 --> 36:54.590
- You take me to your partner,

36:54.590 --> 36:57.384
or you are going to
find out the hard way

36:57.384 --> 36:59.887
how far I am willing to go.

37:02.556 --> 37:05.559
♪

37:06.310 --> 37:09.313
[pinball game beeping]
[door bell jingles]

37:14.776 --> 37:17.446
- [sighs] Here you go.
- Thanks.

37:17.446 --> 37:20.073
[pinball game continues]

37:20.073 --> 37:21.200
- Is that Joe Hardy?

37:21.700 --> 37:22.743
[laughs]

37:23.243 --> 37:24.828
I thought I recognized
the back of your head.

37:26.163 --> 37:27.414
- Good one.

37:27.414 --> 37:29.708
♪ music quietly playing ♪

37:29.708 --> 37:32.544
I'm sorry about the dance.
Okay, I know I said that I--

37:32.544 --> 37:34.546
- I don't want your apology.

37:35.297 --> 37:37.799
Just... call me when
you don't have a case.

37:40.844 --> 37:42.721
PHIL [on video]:
You will find what you dread.

37:42.721 --> 37:45.182
The most dead of the dead.

37:45.182 --> 37:46.808
Beware...

37:46.808 --> 37:48.519
the Bridgeport Demon.

37:48.519 --> 37:49.895
♪ indistinct singing ♪

37:49.895 --> 37:52.272
So, what do you think?

37:53.398 --> 37:54.525
- I have notes.

37:54.525 --> 37:56.068
Lose the poem,

37:56.068 --> 37:58.445
voiceover's not working,
the ending sucks,

37:58.445 --> 38:01.031
and you really think you're
getting a "co-directed by" credit?

38:01.031 --> 38:02.366
- "Additional editing by"?

38:02.366 --> 38:03.659
- No! I have to recut the whole thing!

38:03.659 --> 38:05.452
- Whatever, Dennis!

38:05.452 --> 38:07.412
I'm glad you feel better,
you heinous spaz!

38:07.412 --> 38:10.123
- Why do you love
that poem so much?

38:10.123 --> 38:11.333
[door shuts]

38:11.333 --> 38:13.961
♪

38:13.961 --> 38:15.462
[phone ringing]

38:16.296 --> 38:19.091
- Hello?
WOMAN: Can I speak with Elizabeth Hooper?

38:19.091 --> 38:22.636
- Uh, yeah. Hi, this is Biff.
Or Elizabeth.

38:22.636 --> 38:25.138
WOMAN [on phone]: You left a message
on my answering machine.

38:25.806 --> 38:27.933
- Is this Abigail Owens?

38:27.933 --> 38:29.935
WOMAN:
No, I'm her daughter.

38:29.935 --> 38:32.479
♪

38:32.479 --> 38:33.480
[truck door shuts]

38:37.568 --> 38:38.610
- What's this?

38:39.111 --> 38:41.530
- These are the world-famous
milkshakes from Wilt's

38:41.530 --> 38:43.407
that I still owe you.

38:43.407 --> 38:45.075
- Oh, you mean the ones
you over-hyped so much

38:45.075 --> 38:46.618
it can never live up to my expectations?

38:46.618 --> 38:47.953
[laughs]

38:48.453 --> 38:50.455
- Uh... Mm-hmm.
[laughs]

38:51.832 --> 38:53.750
[laughs] So?

38:55.043 --> 38:57.713
- You got lucky. Yeah.
[laughs]

38:57.713 --> 38:59.756
- Yes, I did.

38:59.756 --> 39:02.217
♪

39:02.217 --> 39:05.053
So, think you're gonna like
living in Bridgeport?

39:08.432 --> 39:10.142
- I think I'm going to love it.

39:10.142 --> 39:11.185
[quiet laugh]

39:11.185 --> 39:14.188
♪

39:16.148 --> 39:17.983
♪

39:17.983 --> 39:19.568
CALLIE:
I thought I'd find you up here.

39:20.027 --> 39:22.029
It's hard to believe
that was only two weeks.

39:22.571 --> 39:25.657
- [scoffs] Time. It's all relative.

39:27.159 --> 39:29.077
- Just glad you're okay.

39:29.077 --> 39:31.580
I thought I lost you in The Sleep Room.

39:31.580 --> 39:34.166
[birds chirping outside]

39:34.166 --> 39:35.209
What's wrong?

39:37.961 --> 39:39.713
- I can't do this anymore.

39:40.547 --> 39:42.841
- It's okay. It's over now.

39:42.841 --> 39:44.885
We've got the whole summer
to get back to normal.

39:45.552 --> 39:48.263
Normal for us, at least.
- I'm not talking about the mysteries.

39:48.889 --> 39:50.390
I'm talking about us.

39:50.390 --> 39:52.059
♪

39:52.059 --> 39:53.727
I'm not happy. I want to break up.

39:55.854 --> 39:58.357
The Eye's been a part of me for so long.

39:59.858 --> 40:01.151
I don't know who I am without it.

40:03.237 --> 40:04.738
I need time to figure it out.

40:05.864 --> 40:07.115
Alone.

40:07.699 --> 40:08.700
- Alone.

40:09.660 --> 40:11.161
After everything we...

40:12.329 --> 40:14.915
You wouldn't have gotten through
any of this if it wasn't for me!

40:14.915 --> 40:16.875
- I'm not trying to hurt you.

40:20.379 --> 40:22.381
You've been a great help.

40:28.136 --> 40:30.264
- Who do you think you are?

40:34.852 --> 40:37.855
[heavy breathing]

40:37.855 --> 40:41.275
[running downstairs]

40:41.817 --> 40:42.818
[door opens]

40:43.694 --> 40:46.488
[creaking]

40:46.488 --> 40:48.907
[footsteps]

40:48.907 --> 40:51.201
♪

40:51.201 --> 40:52.703
[cocks gun]

40:53.412 --> 40:55.080
- Don't move.

40:57.791 --> 40:59.334
Turn around.

40:59.835 --> 41:02.296
WOMAN: Which is it?
Don't move or turn around?

41:05.048 --> 41:06.258
- Turn.

41:13.932 --> 41:15.434
♪

41:15.434 --> 41:17.186
Laura?

41:18.645 --> 41:20.272
[EKG beeping]

41:20.272 --> 41:22.274
[door buzzes, opens]

41:22.274 --> 41:25.277
[quiet hospital chatter]

41:30.115 --> 41:31.116
[door shuts]

41:38.248 --> 41:41.126
♪

41:44.796 --> 41:46.298
[sighs]

41:46.298 --> 41:47.799
- It worked.

41:49.510 --> 41:51.553
It all went according to plan.

41:54.097 --> 41:57.100
Everything The Eye showed me,
I made it happen.

41:57.100 --> 42:00.103
[beeping continues]

42:06.860 --> 42:08.278
We both did.

42:10.322 --> 42:12.366
You did wonderful, Gloria.

42:13.075 --> 42:15.202
My darling daughter.

42:19.081 --> 42:20.624
[jingling]
GEORGE: It's no use.

42:20.624 --> 42:23.418
♪

42:23.418 --> 42:25.254
You can't get out.

42:25.254 --> 42:28.048
You no longer have enough strength.

42:28.048 --> 42:31.802
The power of The Eye
belongs to me once again.

42:32.678 --> 42:34.471
FRANK: No!

42:34.471 --> 42:37.683
[jingling continues]

42:40.561 --> 42:42.980
No no no! No no no no no no no! No!

42:42.980 --> 42:45.315
[whirring]
No!

42:45.315 --> 42:46.233
No no no!

42:46.233 --> 42:48.569
[glitching]: No...
[thud]

42:49.319 --> 42:51.071
- I know I promised I'd return

42:51.071 --> 42:52.990
and I'd explain everything.

42:52.990 --> 42:55.325
[EKG beeping]

42:55.325 --> 42:57.202
Alas, it seems that we don't
have that kind of time.

43:00.747 --> 43:03.000
Where are they, my darling?

43:03.000 --> 43:06.086
Try very hard to tell me.

43:06.879 --> 43:09.006
I need to know, Gloria.

43:10.549 --> 43:12.551
Where did you hide my scrolls?

43:12.551 --> 43:14.011
♪

43:14.011 --> 43:17.014
[EKG beeping faster]

43:20.350 --> 43:23.353
[flat-lining]

43:28.609 --> 43:31.612
♪
